Refer to sceen shot."?>app<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <section>
        <para>The Usage Analytics app creates statistics reports of data analytics usage within the
            DHIS 2 system. Data is collected from Pivot Table, GIS, Event Visualizer, Data
            Visualizer and Event Reports apps.</para>
        <?oxy_comment_start author="CPersson" timestamp="20160427T135337+0200" comment="Info from release notes."?>
        <para>Usage analytics: A new app called Usage Analytics is available and lets you visualize
            statistics on how people (end-users) are utilizing the analytical features of DHIS 2.
            This includes how many times people have loaded charts, pivots, dashboards; how many
            favorites of various kinds people have created and how many people are logging in versus
            total number of users. The system will capture and store daily snapshots of usage
            statistics automatically which can be visualized through this app. </para>
        <?oxy_comment_end?>
        <para>Add info about clicking to hide a series.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Apps</emphasis> menu, click <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Usage Analytics</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select a start date.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an end date.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an interval: day, week month or year.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select a category.</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">FAVORITE
                                <?oxy_comment_start author="CPersson" timestamp="20160427T134118+0200" comment="Add info about toogle options."?>VIEWS<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>:
                            Number of times users have looked at favorites. </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">FAVORITES</emphasis>: Number of
                            <?oxy_comment_start author="CPersson" timestamp="20160426T165827+0200" comment="Must define in which apps.

Consider rewording to &quot;... a saved favorite in the xx, yy ... and zz apps."?>analysis<?oxy_comment_end?>
                            favorites users have created during the selected interval.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">USERS</emphasis>: Number of users in the system
                            during the selected interval.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">UPDATE</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
